{"title":"Ortostatismo iPad-2","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/General/Ortostatismo iPad-2.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Mareo/Vértigo\\NOrtostático\\NHemodinámico","guid":"--L-LtKAq3QF4hz730Pthw","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Definición y\\NTerminología","guid":"3K2-0pxjMpKL0U0q4YWd0Q","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"MAREO/VÉRTIGO ORTOSTÁTICO → síntoma al pasar de decúbito/sentado a bipedestación","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"Cede al sentarse o acostarse","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"SI aparece en decúbito supino → término INAPROPIADO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"1","text":"Hipotensión ortostática (OH) → mecanismo, no síntoma","guid":"","children":[{"id":"6","parent":"5","text":"Caída PAS ≥20 mmHg o PAD ≥10 mmHg en primeros 3 min","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"7","parent":"1","text":"Intolerancia ortostática → término genérico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"8","parent":"1","text":"PRESÍNCOPE → puede ocurrir en cualquier posición (no exclusivo)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"9","parent":"0","text":"Epidemiología","guid":"","children":[{"id":"10","parent":"9","text":"Prevalencia año: 10.9% población general","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"11","parent":"9","text":"Prevalencia de por vida: 12.5%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"12","parent":"9","text":"Adultos mayores >60a: 2-30%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"13","parent":"9","text":"1 de cada 5 adultos >60a en comunidad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"14","parent":"9","text":"1 de cada 4 en centros de largo plazo (ELEAM)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"9","text":"37% de pacientes con OH confirmada → vértigo genuino","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"16","parent":"9","text":"POTS → predominio femenino 5:1,\\Ntípico 15-50 años","guid":"Q11vjA5tq4e0iteLm_BQgw","children":[{"id":"17","parent":"16","text":"Prevalencia estimada 0.2-1% población general","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"18","parent":"16","text":"Mujeres en edad reproductiva → mayoría de casos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"16","text":"Inicio frecuente post-infección viral, embarazo, trauma físico/emocional","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"20","parent":"16","text":"Post-COVID → causa emergente de POTS en todas las edades","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"21","parent":"9","text":"Factores agravantes: esfuerzo físico 53%, calor 32%, posprandial 24%","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"22","parent":"0","text":"Fisiopatología","guid":"","children":[{"id":"23","parent":"22","text":"Al ponerse de pie → 500-700 mL sangre desciende a venous pool esplácnico/MMII","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"24","parent":"22","text":"↓ Retorno venoso → ↓ volumen sistólico → ↓ gasto cardíaco","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"25","parent":"22","text":"Barorreflejo → ↑ FC + vasoconstricción arteriolar compensadora","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"22","text":"Bomba muscular esquelética → mejora retorno venoso","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"22","text":"FALLO COMPENSADOR → ↓ PA → hipoperfusión cerebral global","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"22","text":"Autorregulación cerebral mantiene flujo con PAS 80-150 mmHg","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"22","text":"VÉRTIGO GENUINO →\\Nisquemia focal asimétrica","guid":"Ot-jBiFx1hlPYbB6yHYKEg","children":[{"id":"30","parent":"29","text":"Asimetrías vasculares (estenosis vertebral/basilar) → caída asimétrica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"31","parent":"29","text":"30% con OH profunda → nistagmo rotatorio y hacia abajo en bipedestación","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"32","parent":"22","text":"DISFUNCIÓN AUTONÓMICA → falla simpática adrenérgica","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"33","parent":"0","text":"Clasificación y\\NCriterios\\NDiagnósticos","guid":"wSjTcv982yRimTNG21esRg","children":[{"id":"34","parent":"33","text":"OH INICIAL","guid":"","children":[{"id":"35","parent":"34","text":"Caída PAS >40 mmHg o PAD >20 mmHg en primeros 15 segundos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"34","text":"Transitoria","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"37","parent":"33","text":"RECUPERACIÓN TARDÍA DE PA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"38","parent":"37","text":"Caída ≥20 mmHg a los 30 segundos","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"39","parent":"33","text":"OH CLÁSICA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"40","parent":"39","text":"Caída PAS ≥20 mmHg o PAD ≥10 mmHg en primeros 3 minutos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"41","parent":"39","text":"En hipertensos supinos: usar umbral ≥30 mmHg","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"42","parent":"33","text":"OH TARDÍA (DELAYED OH)","guid":"q15SET--vrZ23ZTHEiQSYg","children":[{"id":"43","parent":"42","text":"Caída ≥20 mmHg DESPUÉS de 3 minutos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"44","parent":"42","text":"↑ Riesgo progresión a OH clásica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"45","parent":"42","text":"Asociada a sinucleinopatías incipientes","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"46","parent":"33","text":"OH NEUROGÉNICA","guid":"UtUCuFKaCFlKwfwXGHhD6w","children":[{"id":"47","parent":"46","text":"Caída PAS ≥30 mmHg o PAD ≥15 mmHg en 3 min","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"48","parent":"46","text":"Falla simpática adrenérgica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"46","text":"PRIMERA MANIFESTACIÓN de Parkinson/sinucleinopatías","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"50","parent":"46","text":"Coexiste con hipertensión supina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"51","parent":"46","text":"Δ[FC]/Δ[PAS] <0.5 lpm/mmHg → sugiere causa neurogénica","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"52","parent":"33","text":"POTS (Síndrome de\\NTaquicardia Postural)","guid":"6RCQSNAo7VMu2QwpqZ7LFA","children":[{"id":"53","parent":"52","text":"DEFINICIÓN → ↑ FC ≥30 lpm en primeros 10 min SIN OH","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"52","text":"O FC ≥120 lpm en bipedestación","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"55","parent":"52","text":"En adolescentes 12-19a: umbral ≥40 lpm","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"56","parent":"52","text":"EXIGE ausencia de OH para el diagnóstico (mutuamente excluyentes)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"57","parent":"52","text":"Fisiopatología (mecanismos múltiples,\\Nfrecuentemente combinados)","guid":"xOJuUU0AzGMOosh6g0dpIA","children":[{"id":"58","parent":"57","text":"Neuropático → denervación simpática selectiva MMII → pooling venoso excesivo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"59","parent":"57","text":"Hiperадrenérgico → ↑ norepinefrina plasmática >600 pg/mL en bipedestación","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"57","text":"Hipovolémico → volumen plasmático reducido ~13% vs controles","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"61","parent":"57","text":"Autoinmune → anticuerpos anti-receptor adrenérgico α1 y β2","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"62","parent":"57","text":"Post-COVID → activación mast cells, microtrombos, disfunción autonómica","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"63","parent":"52","text":"Síntomas acompañantes\\Nfrecuentes","guid":"jkphElWxr2fy9r5gMuh-5g","children":[{"id":"64","parent":"63","text":"Palpitaciones, fatiga severa, niebla mental (brain fog)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"65","parent":"63","text":"Cefalea, intolerancia al ejercicio","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"63","text":"Síntomas gastrointestinales (náuseas, dismotilidad)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"67","parent":"63","text":"Insomnio, dolor generalizado","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"68","parent":"52","text":"Diagnóstico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"69","parent":"68","text":"Prueba de bipedestación activa 10 min con monitoreo continuo FC","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"70","parent":"68","text":"Tilt test: ↑ FC ≥30 lpm sostenido sin caída de PA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"71","parent":"68","text":"Medir norepinefrina supina y de pie (subtipo hiperadrenérgico)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"72","parent":"68","text":"Descartar causas secundarias: anemia, hipertiroidismo, feocromocitoma, mastocitosis","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"73","parent":"52","text":"Manejo","guid":"","children":[{"id":"74","parent":"73","text":"NO FARMACOLÓGICO\\N→ PRIMERA LÍNEA","guid":"iZFMm1GBCATYO_F41DNj4w","children":[{"id":"75","parent":"74","text":"↑ ingesta sal y líquidos (2-3 L/día, 10 g NaCl/día)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"76","parent":"74","text":"Medias de compresión hasta cintura","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"77","parent":"74","text":"Ejercicio progresivo en decúbito/reclinado (natación, remo, bicicleta reclinada)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"78","parent":"74","text":"Evitar calor, alcohol, ayuno prolongado","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"79","parent":"73","text":"FARMACOLÓGICO","guid":"","children":[{"id":"80","parent":"79","text":"Propranolol 10-20 mg → subtipo hiperadrenérgico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"81","parent":"79","text":"Metoprolol → alternativa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"82","parent":"79","text":"Fludrocortisona → hipovolémico (expansión volumen)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"83","parent":"79","text":"Midodrina → vasoconstricción periférica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"84","parent":"79","text":"Ivabradina → ↓ FC sin efecto inotrópico negativo (emergente)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"85","parent":"79","text":"Piridostigmina → mejora transmisión ganglionar autonómica","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"86","parent":"52","text":"En adulto mayor → POTS menos frecuente que OH","guid":"","children":[{"id":"87","parent":"86","text":"Sospechar en frágil con taquicardia ortostática sin caída de PA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"88","parent":"86","text":"Descartar causas secundarias (anemia, ICC, hipertiroidismo) antes de etiquetar","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"89","parent":"0","text":"Criterios Bárány Society\\N(Kim et al. 2019)","guid":"kNrztFfhcw1Mhz_lQ7cxXg","children":[{"id":"90","parent":"89","text":"DEFINITIVO (criterios A+B+C)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"91","parent":"90","text":"A. ≥5 episodios mareo/inestabilidad/vértigo al levantarse → ceden al acostarse","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"92","parent":"90","text":"B. OH, POTS o síncope documentado en bipedestación o tilt test","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"93","parent":"90","text":"C. No explicado por otra enfermedad","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"94","parent":"89","text":"PROBABLE (criterios A+B+C)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"95","parent":"94","text":"A. ≥5 episodios (igual que definitivo)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"96","parent":"94","text":"B. ≥1 síntoma acompañante: debilidad generalizada, dificultad cognitiva, visión borrosa, taquicardia/palpitaciones","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"97","parent":"94","text":"C. No explicado por otra enfermedad","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"98","parent":"0","text":"Presentación\\NClínica","guid":"-HM9odntCs121tGK1htWgQ","children":[{"id":"99","parent":"98","text":"SÍNTOMAS TÍPICOS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"100","parent":"99","text":"Mareo/aturdimiento al levantarse → cede al acostarse","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"101","parent":"99","text":"Visión borrosa o atenuada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"99","text":"Audición amortiguada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"103","parent":"99","text":"CEFALEA EN PERCHA (coat-hanger headache) → occipucio, nuca, hombros","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"104","parent":"99","text":"Debilidad generalizada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"105","parent":"99","text":"Dificultad para concentrarse","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"106","parent":"99","text":"Disnea (desajuste V/Q)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"107","parent":"98","text":"PRESENTACIONES\\NATÍPICAS EN AM","guid":"e_suHaaMDOEQIHN5QmU7SQ","children":[{"id":"108","parent":"107","text":"Caídas inexplicables recurrentes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"109","parent":"107","text":"Síncope sin pródromos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"110","parent":"107","text":"Lentitud cognitiva sin síntomas (DESCONOCIMIENTO HIPOTENSIVO)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"111","parent":"110","text":"Común en sinucleinopatías → Parkinson, DLB, AMS","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"112","parent":"107","text":"Dolor torácico (raro)","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"113","parent":"0","text":"Diagnóstico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"114","parent":"113","text":"ANAMNESIS CLAVE","guid":"","children":[{"id":"115","parent":"114","text":"¿Se marea al acostarse o girar en cama? → Si SÍ, pensar VPPB","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"116","parent":"114","text":"Factores desencadenantes: bipedestación prolongada, comidas ricas en CH, alcohol, calor","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"114","text":"Síntomas autonómicos: estreñimiento, disfunción eréctil, vejiga","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"118","parent":"114","text":"REVISAR FÁRMACOS (causa más frecuente en AM)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"119","parent":"113","text":"PRUEBA DE BIPEDESTACIÓN\\NACTIVA EN CAMA","guid":"ubBpDiDt4rP5xialye1hFA","children":[{"id":"120","parent":"119","text":"5 minutos decúbito supino previo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"121","parent":"119","text":"Mediciones a 1, 2 y 3 minutos tras bipedestación","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"122","parent":"119","text":"Medición adicional a 30 segundos (recuperación tardía)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"123","parent":"119","text":"Manguito a NIVEL DEL CORAZÓN","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"124","parent":"119","text":"Evaluar hipertensión supina (PAS ≥140 o PAD ≥90)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"125","parent":"113","text":"TILT TEST\\N(mesa\\Nbasculante)","guid":"qTC21dWst4_vVb3WsW6CmQ","children":[{"id":"126","parent":"125","text":"Para casos complejos o prueba en cama negativa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"127","parent":"125","text":"Reproducibilidad ASIMÉTRICA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"128","parent":"127","text":"Resultado negativo: ~95% reproducible","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"129","parent":"127","text":"Resultado positivo: ~50% reproducible","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"130","parent":"125","text":"TILT TEST NEGATIVO NO DESCARTA OH","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"131","parent":"113","text":"PRUEBAS FUNCIÓN\\NAUTONÓMICA\\N(especializado)","guid":"qdKbQcxFXDfny973qxfEig","children":[{"id":"132","parent":"131","text":"Maniobra de Valsalva","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"133","parent":"131","text":"Respiración profunda","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"134","parent":"131","text":"Monitoreo ambulatorio PA","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"135","parent":"0","text":"Diagnóstico\\NDiferencial","guid":"3dVB93XW1mT5F0J-xfppHA","children":[{"id":"136","parent":"135","text":"VPPB","guid":"","children":[{"id":"137","parent":"136","text":"Se desencadena también AL ACOSTARSE y girar en cama","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"138","parent":"136","text":"Maniobra Dix-Hallpike positiva","guid":"7OliTcLe5gHReBm16HP2LA","children":[]}]},{"id":"139","parent":"135","text":"PPPD (Mareo\\Npostural-perceptivo\\Npersistente)","guid":"IVdyxIodY6M3OUlIVF60FA","children":[{"id":"140","parent":"139","text":"Gatillado por estímulos visuales complejos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"141","parent":"139","text":"Mejora al tocar objeto fijo (truco somatosensorial) → NO alivia mareo ortostático","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"142","parent":"139","text":"No cede completamente al acostarse","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"143","parent":"135","text":"VESTIBULOPATÍA BILATERAL","guid":"BcogIHPjppu_UJy9w3QX6A","children":[{"id":"144","parent":"143","text":"Inestabilidad ↑ en oscuridad o terreno irregular","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"145","parent":"135","text":"TEMBLOR ORTOSTÁTICO\\NPRIMARIO","guid":"7j3trqzGyaNiXwQVIIUQHA","children":[{"id":"146","parent":"145","text":"Temblor alta frecuencia 14-18 Hz en piernas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"147","parent":"145","text":"Mejora al caminar o sentarse","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"148","parent":"135","text":"TRASTORNOS ANSIEDAD/DEPRESIÓN","guid":"","children":[{"id":"149","parent":"148","text":"Sin cambios hemodinámicos objetivos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"150","parent":"148","text":"PUEDE COEXISTIR con trastornos autonómicos","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"151","parent":"135","text":"NEUROPATÍA SENSITIVA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"152","parent":"151","text":"↓ reflejo aquíleo, parestesias distales, NCS alterado","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"153","parent":"135","text":"SÍNCOPE VASOVAGAL","guid":"","children":[{"id":"154","parent":"153","text":"Distinguir por anamnesis y tilt test","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"155","parent":"0","text":"Pronóstico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"156","parent":"155","text":"CONCEPTO CLAVE → OH es MARCADOR DE RIESGO SISTÉMICO, no solo síntoma local","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"157","parent":"155","text":"Mortalidad","guid":"","children":[{"id":"158","parent":"157","text":"OH neurogénica clásica → mortalidad a 10 años: 64%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"159","parent":"157","text":"OH tardía que progresó a clásica → mortalidad a 10 años: 50%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"160","parent":"157","text":"OH SOSTENIDA → ↑ mortalidad por todas las causas (HR 3.32, IC 95% 1.29-8.50) [Geng et al. 2025]","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"161","parent":"157","text":"OH INICIAL → ↑ MACE (HR 2.38, IC 95% 1.48-3.84) pero SIN ↑ mortalidad aislada [Geng et al. 2025]","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"162","parent":"157","text":"OH en DM2 + HTA (ACCORD trial, n=4266) → ↑ mortalidad total (HR 1.61, IC 95% 1.11-2.36) y ↑ hospitalización/muerte por IC (HR 1.85, IC 95% 1.17-2.93) [Fleg et al. 2016]","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"163","parent":"155","text":"Riesgo\\NCardiovascular","guid":"nzjJimFcRHhi3rTrs9k0kw","children":[{"id":"164","parent":"163","text":"OH inicial y sostenida → ambas ↑ MACE en ≥50 años [Geng et al. 2025]","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"165","parent":"163","text":"OH sostenida: HR 1.77 (IC 95% 1.17-2.69) para eventos cardiovasculares mayores","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"166","parent":"163","text":"↑ Riesgo: enfermedad coronaria, IC, ACV, fibrilación auricular","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"167","parent":"163","text":"HIPERTENSIÓN ORTOSTÁTICA (respuesta paradójica) → mortalidad a 17 años HR 1.40 (IC 95% 1.17-1.68) [Estudio SHEP, Kostis et al. 2019]","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"168","parent":"155","text":"Caídas y\\NFracturas","guid":"Yly4-B5otkJEHr8nLCfYUA","children":[{"id":"169","parent":"168","text":"OH → causa tratable de caídas recurrentes inexplicables","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"170","parent":"168","text":"Caída de 20 mmHg de PAS → doble riesgo de caída traumática","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"171","parent":"168","text":"↑ Riesgo fractura de cadera → institucionalización → mortalidad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"172","parent":"168","text":"Ciclo: OH → caída → fractura → encamamiento → desacondicionamiento → mayor OH","guid":"bUuWuG3nREAOCePFi4NguQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"173","parent":"155","text":"Deterioro\\NCognitivo y\\NDemencia","guid":"NAHRLB_ADi0i89E1XXtanA","children":[{"id":"174","parent":"173","text":"OH → ↑ riesgo demencia y deterioro cognitivo acelerado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"175","parent":"173","text":"Mecanismo: hipoperfusión cerebral crónica → lesión sustancia blanca → disfunción ejecutiva","guid":"BXRyr058usg1iVK2LrSwOg","children":[]},{"id":"176","parent":"173","text":"OH en DLB → disfunción autonómica refleja denervación cardíaca temprana (↑ QTc, ↓ HRV) [Haglund et al. 2024]","guid":"KMPt6_2vv0EDOVlA1Z2Qqg","children":[]},{"id":"177","parent":"173","text":"OH como MARCADOR PRECOZ de sinucleinopatías (Parkinson, DLB, AMS) → antes del diagnóstico formal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"178","parent":"173","text":"OH tardía → asociada a progresión posterior a sinucleinopatía","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"179","parent":"155","text":"Daño de Órgano Diana\\N(OH Neurogénica)","guid":"Y76kCNOUDVtocqJ4MLkOig","children":[{"id":"180","parent":"179","text":"Insuficiencia renal crónica (hipoperfusión renal)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"181","parent":"179","text":"Hipertrofia ventricular izquierda (HTA supina nocturna)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"182","parent":"179","text":"Enfermedad cerebrovascular silente (lesiones sustancia blanca)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"183","parent":"179","text":"Todos asociados a peor supervivencia independiente de otros factores","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"184","parent":"155","text":"Hipertensión Supina\\NCoexistente","guid":"e2WAxcrLMdWVYgjFUb69fQ","children":[{"id":"185","parent":"184","text":"Presente en ~50% de OH neurogénica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"186","parent":"184","text":"↑ Daño órgano diana independientemente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"187","parent":"184","text":"Peor supervivencia que OH sin HTA supina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"188","parent":"184","text":"Dilema terapéutico: tratar OH ↑ HTA supina; tratar HTA supina ↑ OH diurna","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"189","parent":"155","text":"Modificadores\\NPronósticos","guid":"ns8TW782OeFppaiz9YF9jg","children":[{"id":"190","parent":"189","text":"Fragilidad → amplifica riesgo de todos los outcomes adversos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"191","parent":"189","text":"DM2 + OH → sinergia negativa (ACCORD trial: 20% de 4266 pacientes con OH ≥1 vez)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"192","parent":"189","text":"Polifarmacia → OH farmacológica → peor pronóstico que OH primaria si no se corrige","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"193","parent":"189","text":"OH asintomática → TAMBIÉN aumenta riesgo → no ignorar hallazgo incidental","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"194","parent":"155","text":"Pregunta Clave\\NPendiente","guid":"EUTJEXMN4CT8rDcxzHeAyQ","children":[{"id":"195","parent":"194","text":"NO hay RCTs que demuestren que TRATAR la OH mejora mortalidad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"196","parent":"194","text":"Evidencia actual es observacional → asociación ≠ causalidad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"197","parent":"194","text":"Tratamiento justificado por calidad de vida, caídas y funcionalidad","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"198","parent":"0","text":"Manejo","guid":"","children":[{"id":"199","parent":"198","text":"Objetivo → mejorar síntomas y funcionalidad (NO alcanzar PA específica)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"200","parent":"198","text":"NO FARMACOLÓGICO\\N(BASE del tratamiento)","guid":"5qV6I3suAWgHOkSahbctRQ","children":[{"id":"201","parent":"200","text":"EDUCACIÓN","guid":"","children":[{"id":"202","parent":"201","text":"Reconocer síntomas de advertencia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"203","parent":"201","text":"Evitar desencadenantes: bipedestación prolongada, comidas abundantes, alcohol, calor","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"204","parent":"200","text":"REVISIÓN DE FÁRMACOS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"205","parent":"204","text":"Suspender/reducir antihipertensivos, diuréticos, alfa-bloqueadores, antidepresivos","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"206","parent":"200","text":"MANIOBRAS FÍSICAS DE CONTRAPRESIÓN","guid":"","children":[{"id":"207","parent":"206","text":"Cruzar piernas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"208","parent":"206","text":"Ponerse en cuclillas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"209","parent":"206","text":"Tensión muscular (tensar MMII y abdomen)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"210","parent":"206","text":"Aplicar al inicio de síntomas o preventivamente","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"211","parent":"200","text":"INGESTA DE AGUA EN BOLO","guid":"","children":[{"id":"212","parent":"211","text":"500 mL en 2-3 minutos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"213","parent":"211","text":"↑ PA en 5-10 min, dura 30-45 min","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"214","parent":"200","text":"MEDIDAS DIETÉTICAS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"215","parent":"214","text":"Comidas pequeñas y frecuentes, bajo CH","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"216","parent":"214","text":"Sal dietética ~10 g NaCl/día + 2-3 L líquidos/día","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"217","parent":"214","text":"PRECAUCIÓN con sal en hipertensión supina","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"218","parent":"200","text":"EJERCICIO","guid":"","children":[{"id":"219","parent":"218","text":"Entrenamiento fuerza MMII","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"220","parent":"218","text":"Ciclismo reclinado, remo (sin esfuerzo máximo)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"221","parent":"200","text":"MEDIDAS EN CASOS SEVEROS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"222","parent":"221","text":"Elevar cabecera cama 20-30 cm","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"223","parent":"221","text":"Faja abdominal elástica → reduce estancamiento esplácnico","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"224","parent":"198","text":"FARMACOLÓGICO (si persiste con manejo no farmacológico)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"225","parent":"224","text":"MIDODRINA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"226","parent":"225","text":"Agonista α₁-adrenérgico acción corta","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"227","parent":"225","text":"2.5-15 mg 2-3 veces/día","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"228","parent":"225","text":"RAM: hipertensión supina, piloerección, retención urinaria","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"229","parent":"225","text":"FDA aprobada","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"230","parent":"224","text":"DROXIDOPA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"231","parent":"230","text":"Precursor norepinefrina acción corta","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"232","parent":"230","text":"100-600 mg 3 veces/día","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"233","parent":"230","text":"RAM: hipertensión supina, cefalea, náuseas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"234","parent":"230","text":"FDA aprobada","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"235","parent":"224","text":"FLUDROCORTISONA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"236","parent":"235","text":"Mineralocorticoide → expansión volumen","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"237","parent":"235","text":"0.05-0.2 mg/día","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"238","parent":"235","text":"RAM: hipertensión supina, hipokalemia, edema","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"239","parent":"235","text":"NO aprobada FDA para esta indicación","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"240","parent":"224","text":"ACARBOSA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"241","parent":"240","text":"Inhibidor α-glucosidasa → hipotensión POSprandial","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"242","parent":"240","text":"50-150 mg antes de comidas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"243","parent":"240","text":"RAM: gases, distensión abdominal","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"244","parent":"224","text":"PIRIDOSTIGMINA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"245","parent":"244","text":"Inhibidor acetilcolinesterasa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"246","parent":"244","text":"30-60 mg 2-3 veces/día","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"247","parent":"244","text":"RAM: cólicos, diarrea, sialorrea","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"248","parent":"198","text":"HIPERTENSIÓN SUPINA COEXISTENTE","guid":"","children":[{"id":"249","parent":"248","text":"Priorizar tratamiento OH cuando sintomática","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"250","parent":"248","text":"Tolerar HTA supina moderada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"251","parent":"248","text":"Agentes antihipertensivos acción corta antes de acostarse si HTA severa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"252","parent":"248","text":"Elevar cabecera cama 20-30 cm reduce HTA nocturna","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"253","parent":"0","text":"Consideraciones Geriátricas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"254","parent":"253","text":"AM → DESCONOCIMIENTO HIPOTENSIVO más frecuente (sinucleinopatías)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"255","parent":"253","text":"Caídas como ÚNICA manifestación → buscar activamente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"256","parent":"253","text":"Fármacos como causa principal en AM → REVISAR SIEMPRE (STOPP)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"257","parent":"256","text":"Antihipertensivos, diuréticos, alfa-bloqueadores (tamsulosina), antidepresivos, antipsicóticos","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"258","parent":"253","text":"Hipovolemia relativa → dieta pobre, uso diuréticos, calor","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"259","parent":"253","text":"Disfagia farmacológica → dificulta hidratación y farmacoterapia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"260","parent":"253","text":"Proporcionalidad terapéutica → en frágil severo o terminal, foco en calidad de vida y prevención caídas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"261","parent":"253","text":"CONECTAR CON → VGI dominio fragilidad y caídas","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"262","parent":"0","text":"Perlas Clínicas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"263","parent":"262","text":"PREGUNTAR siempre si se marea al acostarse → diferencia VPPB de OH","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"264","parent":"262","text":"VÉRTIGO GENUINO puede ser OH → isquemia asimétrica da rotación y nistagmo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"265","parent":"262","text":"CEFALEA EN PERCHA → pensar en falla autonómica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"266","parent":"262","text":"TILT TEST NEGATIVO no descarta → usar criterios PROBABLE con síntomas acompañantes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"267","parent":"262","text":"TRUCO SOMATOSENSORIAL → paciente que mejora al tocar objeto = PPPD, no OH","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"268","parent":"262","text":"POTS y OH son MUTUAMENTE EXCLUYENTES por definición","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"269","parent":"262","text":"MAREO RESIDUAL post-Epley exitoso → sospechar OH concomitante","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"270","parent":"262","text":"AM con caídas inexplicables → medir PA ortostática siempre","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"271","parent":"262","text":"Midodrina → no dar >4h antes de acostarse (riesgo HTA supina nocturna)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"272","parent":"262","text":"Droxidopa → especialmente útil en OH neurogénica (Parkinson)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"273","parent":"0","text":"VER TAMBIÉN","guid":"","children":[{"id":"274","parent":"273","text":"→ Presbistasis (Módulo 2 - ORL Geriátrica)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"275","parent":"273","text":"→ Caídas en el Adulto Mayor (Geriatría)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"276","parent":"273","text":"→ Fragilidad y VGI (Valoración Geriátrica)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"277","parent":"273","text":"→ Síncope (Cardiología Geriátrica)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"278","parent":"273","text":"→ Enfermedad de Parkinson y Disautonomía","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"279","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"280","parent":"279","text":"1. Kim HA, Bisdorff A, Bronstein AM, et al. Hemodynamic orthostatic dizziness/vertigo: Diagnostic criteria. Consensus document of the Bárány Society. J Vestib Res. 2019;29(2-3):45-56.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"281","parent":"279","text":"2. Lahrmann H, Cortelli P, Hilz M, et al. EFNS guidelines on the diagnosis and management of orthostatic hypotension. Eur J Neurol. 2006;13(9):930-6.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"282","parent":"279","text":"3. Freeman R, Wieling W, Axelrod FB, et al. Consensus statement on the definition of orthostatic hypotension. Clin Auton Res. 2011;21(2):69-72.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"283","parent":"279","text":"4. Palma JA, Kaufmann H. Diagnosis and management of orthostatic hypotension. Nat Rev Neurol. 2024;20(3):171-87.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":283,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"General","folder":"Entidades clínicas/General","filename":"Ortostatismo iPad-2","id":"map_828","resolved_references":[]}